# S3 — buckets & objects

**Objects** in **buckets**, addressed by a string **key**.

## The model

- **Bucket** — container, **globally unique** name (3–63 chars, lowercase)
- **Object** — file + metadata, keyed by a string
- **S3 is flat** — `a/b/photo.jpg` is one key; "folders" are just rendered prefixes

## The numbers

- Bucket lives in **one region** (stays unless you replicate)
- Object **0 B – 5 TB**; single PUT ≤ **5 GB** → **multipart** above (rec. > 100 MB)
- **No object-count limit**; request capacity scales **per prefix**

Buckets + objects + keys = the whole core. **Everything else bolts on.**
